<title>My First Web Application</title>
  <h1>Welcome to my application!</h1>

  Application Description:
  <br>
  -This method concatenates given arrays and computes mean of the larger (concatenated) array and returns both mean and k'th order statistic of the larger array.
  <br>
  -In the ascending sorted array k'th order statistic means k'th smallest element.
  <br>
  <br>

  User Guide:
  <br>
  * First, second and third form represents array1, array2 and array3 respectively.
  <br>
  * In the first, second and third form, enter a list of doubles seperated by a newline character.
  <br>
  * Fourth form represents k.
  <br>
  * In the fourth form enter an integer. ( k must be >0 and < sum of all arrays lengths)
  <br>
  * If parameters are valid, then mean of the larger array and k'th order statistic of the larger array will be printed. 
  <br>
  <br>

    {{mean}}
    <br>
    {{kth}}

  <form action="compute" method="post">
        <textarea name="input1" rows="10" cols="30"></textarea>
        <textarea name="input2" rows="10" cols="30"></textarea>
        <textarea name="input3" rows="10" cols="30"></textarea>
        <textarea name="input4" rows="10" cols="30"></textarea>
        <br>
        <input type="submit">
  </form>
